
[1]empalement

   EMPA'LEMENT, n. A fencing, fortifying or inclosing with stakes; a
   putting to death by thrusting a stake into the body.

   1. In botany, the calyx or flower-cup of a plant, which surrounds the
   fructification, like a fence of pales.

   2. In heraldry, a conjunction of coats of arms, pale-wise.
